          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Simultaneous evaluation of the thermal-neutron",
                " absorption cross sections of H, Mn and S was made by",
                " analyzing different values measured by different",
                " authors.",
                "Simultaneous evaluation is essential because the",
                " quantity measured in the Mn-bath dilution technique",
                " is dependent on the values assumed for the cross",
                " sections of S and Mn at the time of the measurement.",
                "Input data",
                " Ref.   Measured function             Value   Unc.",
                " MU1981 sigH                          0.3326    (7)",
                " MU1981 sigMn                        13.3       (2)",
                " AX1982 F*(sigH/sigMn)/(1+sigS/sigMn) 0.024773 (92)*",
                " SM1984 F*(sigH/sigMn)/(1+sigS/sigMn) 0.024762 (56)*",
                " AX1985 F*(sigH/sigMn)/(1+sigS/sigMn) 0.024790 (79)*",
                " AR1986 sigS/sigH                     1.621    (33)",
                " MU1981 sigS                          0.5280  (108)",
                " VE1982 sigS                          0.543     (9)",
                " RA1985 sigS                          0.516    (15)",
                " *: These original values were corrected:",
                "  0.024773 -> 0.024792",
                "  0.024762 -> 0.024788",
                "  0.024790 -> 0.024818"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "DATA-ERR",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The uncertainties of the ratio measurements",
                " do not include the uncertainties in F(which is a",
                " factor that represents the values of (1+sigS/sigMn)",
                " assumed by the various authors) due to the uncertainty",
                " of sigs,which, in some of the values were included as",
                " correlated uncertainties"
              ]
            }
          ],
